The transfer system works well when passengers understand its operational constraints and plan accordingly. Booking with appropriate advance notice, allowing extra time for connections, and maintaining flexibility during weather or disruption events leads to successful travel experiences. The key insight I gained from my equipment coordination challenges was recognizing that Colorado transfers function as integrated logistics networks rather than simple passenger shuttles.
